This example is an adaptation of the example in examples/HydroTests/BalsaraKim where we use stars and
stellar feedback to inject energy, instead of relying on a forcing scheme. To recap, this example is based 
on the supernova-driven turbulence test from Balsara & Kim (2004) and Price (2018), only without MHD.

It consists of a series of energetic supernova events in a patch of ISM. These injections will form 
interacting shock shells driving turbulence (and magnetic field amplification), and in turn result in a 
filamentary structure.

Running the test
________________

configure swift as:
./configure --with-chemistry=EAGLE --with-cooling=EAGLE --with-stars=EAGLE --with-feedback=EAGLE --with-ext-potential=constant --with-kernel=quintic-spline --disable-hand-vec

You can set up the example with the run script:
./run.sh


Analysing the Snapshots
_______________________

To analyse the snapshots you can run the following

python3 PlotResult.py
